parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A crack in the frame weld point can compromise the structural integrity of the motorcycle, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Cracking or breaking of the frame weld point on the right side
typically above the clutch cover
with no prior incident or damage to the motorcycle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stator can cause the electrical system to fail, leading to a loss of power, battery failure, and potentially causing the engine to seize, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine warning light illuminates
battery failure
inability to bump start
unbalanced stator rotation
magnets on the ends of the stator falling off
pieces of the alternator fracturing and falling into the crankcase.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rotor assembly can cause the electrical system to fail, leading to a loss of power, battery failure, and potentially causing the engine to seize, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Similar to stator failure
including the check engine warning light illuminating
battery failure
inability to bump start
unbalanced rotor rotation
pieces of the alternator fracturing and falling into the crankcase.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked frame weld can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, affecting its handling and stability, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: A small
barely visible crack in the frame weld
typically located on the right side where the two sections of the frame meet
above the centerline of the clutch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the frame weld can cause a loss of structural integrity, leading to a potential loss of control or accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Weld seam failure on the right side of the frame below the fuel tank
frame cracking or breaking
unusual noises or vibrations while riding.
